1. Create a sample react app
Let’s create a simple react application using the create-react-app and handle an email validation message based on the given input.

Look at the app.js component for the react app.

Let’s test the following use cases for the above application.

*render email input

Assert

1.The input field should be in the document
2.The input field should have a type email attribute

*pass valid email to test email input field

Assert

1.The input field have a valid given value
2.The error message should not be in the document

*pass invalid email to test input value

Assert

1.The input field have an invalid given value
2The error message should be in the document
3The error message should contain “Please enter a valid email.” text

Here, we will use the userEvent from the @testing-library/user-event to type the text in the input field.
